column5: Cutting wood, moving logs, installing fences, building the garden, random ATVing, bonfires, breeding some rabbits (bow chicka...) aaaaannnd, hopefully a few casts for trout.
Heading up to the Fish Kincardine Salmon Derby,.  Always a great time.. Now if the wind just co-operates Good luck...(hint green patch)  Building my big ass smoker and a fence

Oh and if there's any question.....They're Here!!!   Well you just messed my day up, now I'll have that song stuck in it! I'll be fishing resident trout today and then maybe some more of the same or pike tomorrow, Monday not sure...
Buddy's new boat.     Might be slimed tomorrow.
Ah,that new boat smell. Nice ride yer buddys got there Rob.
Just worked 3 12hr days.... With a 4th tomorrow, but at triple time I will be laughing as I watch each minute go by  works out to 1.30 each and every minute.... I couldn't say no!  G
I worked, and fished every day so far. Fishing all day tomorrow too. Eyes and crappies are on fire!  S.
Had a great day of Crappie fishing yesterday at a lake just outside of the city (Girlfriend outfished me again) now today debating a couple different lakes.
First fish was an OOS bass that Ryan caught on a 5 ft ultralight rod. He did real well fighting it.      Spot the city kids in the country.     Ready to go to work tomorrow and have a rest.
Now that everyone has fed the bugs.... I think it's time to go North !!
Crappies, pike, more crappies a few OOS bass, resident browns, lots of black flies.  Pretty much sums up my weekend.
Lots of black flies and no lakers. Wont go there again till the bass opens.
Tried some ice breaking:In attempts to find some of theseBut being Lac des Milles Lac you knew you'd be seeing some of these slimy guys... http://youtu.be/66tznHfDO9M
What is everyone up to?  I am taking my 6 year old to Rice for 2 days.  First soft water trip of the year....soooooo pumped!!!!
At bay of quinte waiting for the wind to die down so I can get out for a fish.

good luck on Rice, let us know how you do  for me, walleye in Haliburton and the Kawarthas, hoping to launch the pontoon and look for lakers too, if things go well, a fish fry dinner and campfire, probably cutting and splitting some wood, it should be fun
A last run Sunday in my now sold kayak...
Fishing local with my brother Friday, then Tillsonburg for the weekend. Memorial Cup game Saturday and maybe a trip to pick -up my friend's new boat. Maybe a test run.
Lakers,lakers,lakers,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,, Did I say lakers?  ,If it,s flat out there, jig for some whities. Then hit the streams and might even brave the tube with the cold waters for perch and crappies.
My rivers are blown , so I'll watch the grass grow, then I'll watch  the memorial cup.
Going up to Huntsville on Saturday and Sunday for my very first tournament. A pike tournament. Then on Monday I'll be checking out some new spots with a buddy of mine up in the kawartha highlands.
Watch the ice melt  while installing a new metal roof!!
then Tillsonburg for the weekend.  my back still aches when I hear that word  good luck, let us know how you do Locnar, suspending jerk baits were the ticket in last weeks pike derby on Balsam
I was hoping to go to Rice. Or the cottage. Depends on the weather. Its not looking good now.
searching for the spring king

my back still aches when I hear that word  good luck, let us know how you do Locnar, suspending jerk baits were the ticket in last weeks pike derby on Balsam  Nice Stompin Tom reference haha.  Suspending jerkbaits eh, a nice slow presentation? Perch coloration be alright?
Working......

Nice Stompin Tom reference haha.  Suspending jerkbaits eh, a nice slow presentation? Perch coloration be alright?  try to find the warmest water, it doesn't have to be dead slow, sure, try perch color, if not something brighter (I'm not an expert, just going by what was happening last weekend), good luck again
Kiiiiipawa
Whatever we're all doin---be careful on those roads  Jam packed long weekends put people in a hurry  My mother used to remind me----better to go a bit slower and make sure you get there
I'm going to watch hockey, drink large amounts of rum and lay a bunch of patio stones around the house.

Went down to bp and sail with some old gift cards and stocked up for my pike trip starting next fri. Also picked up some things to get a little more serious on my backyard carpin. Im hoping to test some stuff out saturday after work( i tied my first hair rig today
Oh and if there's any question.....They're Here!!!
trying to find a partner in crime and maybe hit southern Georgian bay.......anyone interested??
Rice Lake Saturday, family day Sunday and Lake St John Victoria Day Monday.
Ripping up the old carpet in the basement @ the cottage and maybe I might get to wet a line for some pike..... maybe.
